text:p.text:span: C U R R I C U L U M V I T A E
I thoroughly enjoy working within new environments and seeing how my skills and
experience can be contributed to and adapted to maximise efficiency within any
workplace. This included working within time-sensitive conditions and being able to
cope under pressure. Due to my working ethic, I can confidently contribute to a
business to help them provide quality services on which customers depend.
I am well-mannered and have worked hard to achieve excellence in everything I do. I
have an excellent record of attendance and I am determined to achieve my goals. I
am confident in a group situation and thoroughly enjoy learning as part of a team. I
also enjoy sharing my knowledge with others, particularly in areas that I am
passionate about. During my time at school, I have actively participated in
extracurricular activities, going above and beyond the requirements of a student and
often out of my comfort zone. I am proud of my achievements which include
becoming an anti-bullying ambassador, student year leader, Year 11 Student
Councillor, Prefect and Student Head of House. Throughout these roles, I have
worked closely with other students and Senior Team Leadership adults to organise
events to bring the school community together, provide support for my peers and I
have been at the forefront of reviews to better the school environment overall and
maintain high standards and student expectations. My ability to care for and support
others is important for me as well as taking ownership and leadership.
I work within a range of job roles that require precision in customer & tenant
satisfaction as well as keeping up to date with laws and regulations in
telecommunications, education and standardisation, Corporate ISO, E-commerce,
and Distrubution.
